The All Progressives Congress, APC, presidential candidate, Bola Tinubu and President Muhammadu Buhari are meeting behind closed-doors. The meeting, which has the Katsina State Governor, Bello Masari in attendance, is holding in Daura, Buhari’s home town in Katsina State. Masari had earlier received Tinubu at the Umaru Musa Yar’Adua International Airport enroute Daura. This is coming at a time Tinubu was widely reported to have picked former Borno State governor, Senator Kashim Shettima as his running mate. Tinubu had submitted the name of Kabiru Masari to the Independent National Electoral Commission, INEC, as a place holder ahead of the deadline set by the commission. Masari hails from Katsina State.